I"<p>Actors are only the building-blocks of async programs.</p>

<p>It is possible to build spaghetti-Architectures with Actors.</p>

<p>Similar to the suggestions in “GOTO Considered Harmful”, one needs to find ways to structure Actor-based system designs.</p>

<p>[Aside: people avoid message-based systems because early message-based systems were flat and tangled - something that a good dollop of structuring could fix].</p>

